description: Formed from Latin umbilicus (“navel”) + the suffix -al; surface analysis, umbilic- +‎ -al.

adjectives.description: umbilical (comparative more umbilical, superlative most umbilical)

entries.meaning: Of, or relating to, the navel (umbilicus) or the umbilical cord.
(mathematics) Such that the curvatures of normal sections are all equal to each other.
(astronautics) A cord connecting an astronaut to a spacecraft, or a craft to ground control prior to launch, etc.
